Guiding Light.I DESC: The final terminal will be highlighted with a glowing blue outline, leading you straight to your last objective.
Guiding Light.II DESC: The final two terminal will be highlighted with a glowing blue outline, leading you straight to your last objective.
Guiding Light.III DESC: Each time a terminal is hacked, all other available terminals will be highlighted temporarily.

Adrenaline Boost.I DESC: Saving a teammate ignites a surge of energy. Gain a 3 seconds speed boost after a successful rescue.
Adrenaline Boost.II DESC: Saving a teammate ignites a surge of energy. Gain a 5 seconds speed boost after a successful rescue.
Adrenaline Boost.III DESC: Saving a teammate ignites a surge of energy. Gain a 7 seconds speed boost after a successful rescue.

Lone Survivor.I DESC: When the odds are against you, your determination heightens. Decoding speed increases by 20% with each eliminated survivor.
Lone Survivor.II DESC: When the odds are against you, your determination heightens. Decoding speed increases by 50% with each eliminated survivor.
Lone Survivor.III DESC: When the odds are against you, your determination heightens. Decoding speed increases by 80% with each eliminated survivor.

Healing Hands.I DESC: Your swift hands mend wounds faster, allowing you to heal temmates 10% quicker.
Healing Hands.II DESC: Your swift hands mend wounds faster, allowing you to heal temmates 25% quicker.
Healing Hands.III DESC: Your swift hands mend wounds faster, allowing you to heal temmates 40% quicker.

Locked Eyes.I DESC: Temporarily highlights the locations of all other survivors for 6 seconds after completing a terminal.
Locked Eyes.II DESC: Temporarily highlights the locations of all other survivors for 10 seconds after completing a terminal.
Locked Eyes.III DESC: Temporarily highlights the locations of all other survivors for 14 seconds after completing a terminal.

Pitfall.I DESC: Allows you to sabotage a ball pit, making it inaccessible for 20 seconds.
Pitfall.II DESC: Allows you to sabotage a ball pit, making it inaccessible for 40 seconds.
Pitfall.III DESC: Allows you to sabotage a ball pit, making it inaccessible for 60 seconds.

Clocking Out.I DESC: After completing a terminal, gain a speed boost for 5 seconds.
Clocking Out.II DESC: After completing a terminal, give yourself and any nearby survivors a speed boost for 3 seconds.
Clocking Out.III DESC: After hacking all terminals, give yourself a minor speed boost for the rest of the match. This effect works until any damage is taken.

Dusting Off.I DESC: When completing a healing action on another survivor, reduce their capture progress by 5%.
Dusting Off.II DESC: When completing a healing action on another survivor, reduce their capture progress by 10%, It'll also reduce your capture progress by 5%.
Dusting Off.III DESC: When completing a healing action on another survivor, reduce their capture progress by 15%, It'll also reduce your capture progress by 8%.

Hidden Charge.I DESC: Even in failure, you remain unnoticed. Failing to hack a terminal will not alert the animatronic. (3 use)
Hidden Charge.II DESC: Even in failure, you remain unnoticed. Failing to hack a terminal will not alert the animatronic. (4 uses)
Hidden Charge.III DESC: Even in failure, you remain unnoticed. Failing to hack a terminal will not alert the animatronic. (5 uses)

Third Eye.I DESC: After hacking all terminals, your instincts sharpen, revealing the animatronic's location for 5 seconds.
Third Eye.II DESC: After hacking all terminals, your instincts sharpen, revealing the animatronic's location for 10 seconds.
Third Eye.III DESC: After hacking all terminals, your instincts sharpen, revealing the animatronic's location for the rest of the match.

Self Care.I DESC: Grants you an item that let you heal for 30 seconds with a 240 seconds cooldown.
Self Care.II DESC: Grants you an item that let you heal for 30 seconds with a 180 seconds cooldown.
Self Care.III DESC: Grants you an item that let you heal for 30 seconds with a 120 seconds cooldown.

Shielded Escape.I DESC: Rescuing a teammate from a ball pit grants you a temporary force field, protecting you and teammate from the next hit. Lasts 1 seconds.
Shielded Escape.II DESC: Rescuing a teammate from a ball pit grants you a temporary force field, protecting you and teammate from the next hit. Lasts 1.5 seconds.
Shielded Escape.III DESC: Rescuing a teammate from a ball pit grants you a temporary force field, protecting you and teammate from the next hit. Lasts 2 seconds.

Tank Build.I DESC: While hacking a terminal you only take 35 damage if attacked.
Tank Build.II DESC: 35% chance to reduce damage taken when attacked to 35.
Tank Build.III DESC: Increase max health by 50, but your walkspeed is reduced by 10%.

Trimmers.I DESC: While nearby a survivor being carried, boost their escape progress by 10%. If they manage to escape you will be slowed down 20% for 3 seconds.
Trimmers.II DESC: While nearby a survivor being carried, boost their escape progress by 20%. If they manage to escape you will be slowed down 20% for 3 seconds.
Trimmers.III DESC: While nearby a survivor being carried, boost their escape progress by 30%. If they manage to escape you will be slowed down 20% for 3 seconds.

Sprint.I DESC: Gain a speed boost for 5 seconds with a 40 seconds cooldown.
Sprint.II DESC: Gain a speed boost for 5 seconds with a 35 seconds cooldown.
Sprint.III DESC: Gain a speed boost for 5 seconds with a 30 seconds cooldown.

Rekindle.I DESC: If you are the last survivor you gain a permanent 10% speed boost.
Rekindle.II DESC: If you are the last survivor you open doors 15% faster and hack terminals 5% faster.
Rekindle.III DESC: If you are the last survivor you gain a 10% speed boost, open doors 15% faster and hack terminals 5% faster.

Guardian Angel.I DESC: After you capture percentage reaches 95% you'll be rescued. 1 time use.
Guardian Angel.II DESC: After you capture percentage reaches 90% you'll be rescued. 1 time use.
Guardian Angel.III DESC: After you capture percentage reaches 85% you'll be rescued. 1 time use.

Resolve.I DESC: After being rescued, gain a 5% speed boost for 3 seconds.
Resolve.II DESC: After being rescued, gain a 7% speed boost for 4 seconds.
Resolve.III DESC: After being rescued, gain a 10% speed boost for 5 seconds.

Dim Presence.name: Dim Presence
Dim Presence.desc: Darkness works in favor of the animatronic. Reduces the range of the glow by 10%/20%/30%, making it easier to creep up on unsuspecting survivors.

Predators Trail.name: Predators Trail
Predators Trail.desc: Fresh wounds leave a path to follow. After striking a survivor, their footprints become visible for 1/2/3 seconds, making it easier to track them down.

Rescue Signal.name: Rescue Signal
Rescue Signal.desc: A rescue won't go unheard. The animatronic is alerted when a survivor has been rescued for a ball pit, temporarily highlighting its and its escape's location for 1/2/3 seconds.

Brute Force.name: Brute Force
Brute Force.desc: Nothing stands in the way. Opens doors 10%/20%/30% faster, reducing obstacles between the animatronic and its prey.

Listening Mode.name: Listening Mode
Listening Mode.desc: Silence sharpens the senses. While standing still, activates ability to detect survivors hacking nearby. A distinct sound or notification alerts both the animatronic and survivors if detected. Lasts 1/2/3 seconds.

Final Stand.name: Final Stand
Final Stand.desc: The hunt isn't over yet. When the exit doors are unlocked, the animatronic's speed increases by 10%/15%/25%, making last-minute escapes even more dangerous.

Marked One.name: Marked One
Marked One.desc: Strikes leave a lasting mark. When a survivor is hit, nearby teammates will be revealed with a red outline for a short duration.

Sugar Crash.name: Sugar Crash
Sugar Crash.desc: Can throw a cupcake at the nearby survivor to deal damage and weaken their escape.

Amplified Fear.name: Amplified Fear
Amplified Fear.desc: Strums a chilling chord, sending shockwaves that slow down nearby survivors in the animatronic's presence.

Circuit Breaker.name: Circuit Breaker
Circuit Breaker.desc: The hooked metal hand can temporarily sabotage terminals by striking them, stalling survivors and slowing their progress.

Springlocked.name: Springlocked
Springlocked.desc: Instantly knocks survivors with a powerful attack. Passive cooldown 45 seconds.

Mangled.name: Mangled
Mangled.desc: Can grab the nearest survivor within 60 studs (Dodgeable). 30 seconds cooldown.

Silent Steps.name: Silent Steps
Silent Steps.desc: Silences footsteps and camera shake influence for 5/9/13 seconds, making attacks more surprising. 30 seconds cooldown.

Short Circuit.name: Short Circuit
Short Circuit.desc: Resets the progress of the nearest terminal. 90 seconds cooldown.

Vengeance.name: Vengeance
Vengeance.desc: When a survivor is downed, anyone within 35 studs of the downed survivor is instantly struck with residual damage.

Scorchpath.name: Scorchpath
Scorchpath.desc: Can create a blazing wall of fire anywhere, forming a temporary barrier of heat that punishes anyone who dares to cross it.
Scorchpath.lvl100: Slightly wider blazing wall of fire (10%).

Companion Bear.name: Companion Bear
Companion Bear.desc: A little companion plushie that can be placed anywhere, once placed, it grants the ability to teleport back to the plushie.

Ice Cream Lure.name: Ice Cream Lure
Ice Cream Lure.desc: Drops an ice cream cone that detects nearby survivors. Can be removed by survivors.

Deadly Grace.name: Deadly Grace
Deadly Grace.desc: Twirls around during sprints, dealing low damage (20) around itself with each spin, but the spring has a 300% longer cooldown.

Limb Reaper.name: Limb Reaper
Limb Reaper.desc: Hitting a survivor will cause them to lose a limb that will either reduce movement speed or hacking speed. Survivors can retrieve their limbs.
Limb Reaper.lvl100:
25% chance to get two limbs at once.
Also a chance to get a second limb appears.

Bon Bon Bite.name: Bon Bon Bite
Bon Bon Bite.desc: Attacking a survivor will poison every nearby survivors for 10 damage every seconds for 5 seconds. 30 seconds cooldown.

Remote Anchor.name: Remote Anchor
Remote Anchor.desc: Animatronic can drop a trap that trips survivors.

Please Stand By.name: Please Stand By
Please Stand By.desc: Some terminals are trapped. Hacking a trapped terminal grants the animatronic a speed boost and cooldown reduction.
Please Stand By.lvl100: Extra terminal (Half the % from the speed boost).

Digital Reality.name: Digital Reality
Digital Reality.desc: Transfers into the digital reality by becoming invisible for a while. When turning visible, cannot move and attack for a split second. 35 seconds cooldown.

Silent Angel.name: Silent Angel
Silent Angel.desc: The angels burn animatronic's eyes, it can't look at them for long... But they can't move while it does. The animatronic can teleport to any angel.

Ignited One.name: Ignited One
Ignited One.desc: Strikes leave a lasting mark. When a survivor is hit, nearby teammates will be revealed with a red outline for a short duration. Anyone in the ability's range will temporarily lose the ability to crawl.

Toxic Crash.name: Toxic Crash
Toxic Crash.desc: Can throw a cupcake a toxic cupcake that creates a toxic cloud.

Amplified Terror.name: Amplified Terror
Amplified Terror.desc: Strums a chilling chord, blinding and slowing nearby survivors.

Blackout Breaker.name: Blackout Breaker
Blackout Breaker.desc: The hooked metal hand can temporarily sabotage terminals by striking them and regresses progress by 15%. Can only be used 2 times on the same terminal.

The Joy Of Creation.name: The Joy Of Creation
The Joy Of Creation.desc: Animatronic emits a searing pulse, scorching survivors. If they are caught in the pulse, they leave burning marks.

Snowfall.name: Snowfall
Snowfall.desc: Animatronic stands still and channels its power, emitting a large freezing area.

Festive Distraction.name: Festive Distraction
Festive Distraction.desc: Animatronic drops three brightly wrapped gift boxes in a cluster. Anyone caught in the radius will be disoriented. For every caught survivor Animatronic receives a temporary small burst of speed.

Please Deposit 5 Coins.name: Please Deposit 5 Coins
Please Deposit 5 Coins.desc: Survivors must collect coins around the map. Every 2 minutes Animatronic will ask for 5 coins. If any survivors don't have that many, they will marked until they collect enough.

Guitar Hunt.name: Guitar Hunt
Guitar Hunt.desc: The animatronic's guitar will spawn somewhere on the map. If found by survivors, it won't be able to use abilities. If it isn't found, survivors will be slowed until it's found. If the animatronic finds their guitar, they'll be able to use it to slow down survivors, but after a while it'll disappear and they'll have to look for it again.

SQUAWK!.name: SQUAWK!
SQUAWK!.desc: The Animatronic spawns with a parrot that perches on a random terminal in the map. When that terminal is hacked, the parrot will warn it.

Rockstar's Dream.name: Rockstar's Dream
Rockstar's Dream.desc: The Rockstars yearn to show their musical talents to others. If they haven't hit anyone in 20 seconds, they get a speed boost until they hit someone.

Undying Will.name: Undying Will
Undying Will.desc: For every capture Animatronic gets, it will get a small buff to his stats.

Once Upon A Time.name: Once Upon A Time
Once Upon A Time.desc: Animatronic will occasionally scare the survivors.

Downed Transmission.name: Downed Transmission
Downed Transmission.desc: The Animatronic has the ability to put knocked survivor into a random ballpit instantly if a box isn't winded, but it's speed will weaken temporarily.

Clawed Attack.name: Clawed Attack
Clawed Attack.desc: The Animatronic's piercing claw sets a bleedout timer and a bloodtrail. The survivor has 1 minute to heal or they go knocked.
Clawed Attack.lvl100: Attacked survivor will be knocked in 8 seconds.

Bayou Breach.name: Bayou Breach
Bayou Breach.desc: The animatronic can burst through doors, leaving them permanently broken.

Shooting Star.name: Shooting Star
Shooting Star.desc: The animatronic is able to dash forward 3 times.

Rabbit's Calling.name: Rabbit's Calling
Rabbit's Calling.desc: The animatronic passively disorients survivors around them.

Moonlight.name: Moonlight
Moonlight.desc: You can't outrun it... The Animatronic places its hat down, slowing survivors nearby.

Cleanup Time.name: Cleanup Time
Cleanup Time.desc: Have to be quick to keep tidy! The Animatronic drops a barrel that'll speed its up when it's nearby.

Fan of Ruin.name: Fan of Ruin
Fan of Ruin.desc: Animatronic throws their fan at the nearest survivor, dealing damage and reducing their HP. A successful hit temporarily boosts their fanning speed, which increases their movement speed.

Dragons Wrath.name: Dragons Wrath
Dragons Wrath.desc: Hitting survivors fuels the Animatronic's fury, allowing them to eventually unleash their wrath. Once charged, animatronic rains down fireballs on key locations like terminals and ballpits.
